  "response_text": "Inside a small fast-food shop or sandwich counter, a heavyset middle-aged man in a white cook’s jacket, white apron, and white paper cap holds a wall telephone to his ear. Behind him are brick walls, drink machines, and bright menu boards with small lettering; “PIZZA” and a pasta sign are partly visible. Long rolls or loaves sit in a row along the counter to his right. He looks startled and urgent, clutching the phone, pointing, and leaning forward as if giving quick instructions. Another worker in a similar white cap appears behind the counter, watching and then moving to help.\n\nThe cook turns away from the phone and reaches across the counter toward an enormous, extra-long loaf. He lifts the bulky bread under one arm like a log while the other worker crouches down and pulls out supplies from below the counter. Containers, trays, and sandwich-making items come into view as both workers scramble. The mood is busy and comic because the food is oversized and the workers are rushing to gather everything.\n\nOutside, a yellow AMC Pacer is parked by the storefront. The car has a rounded, compact body, large curved windows, and a wide-looking cabin. It then appears driving along a tree-lined residential street. The yellow car moves smoothly on the road, with lawns, parked cars, and tall trees passing around it.\n\nInside the Pacer, the sandwich maker sits in the back, dressed in the same white uniform and cap. The wide rear seat area gives him enough room to work with a very long sandwich laid across a board or tray spanning nearly the width of the car. The sandwich is open-faced at first, with rows of sliced tomatoes, meats, and other fillings arranged along the bread. A small roll of paper towels and food containers sit nearby. As the car moves, he leans over the sandwich and continues assembling it, using a pan or tray of ingredients and carefully placing items along the length of the bread while scenery slides past the side windows.\n\nThe yellow Pacer turns through a quiet, leafy street. From outside, it curves around a corner and continues down the road without any visible swaying or trouble. Back inside, the cook holds a small ingredient in one hand and a long thin pick or skewer in the other. A closer look shows his hands delicately handling a small green garnish, likely an olive or pickle piece, as he threads or prepares it for the sandwich. The oversized sandwich remains directly below his hands.\n\nIn the front seat, another middle-aged man in a white paper cap drives. He has glasses and a moustache, with the steering wheel in front of him and trees passing outside. He glances back while tasting something from his fingers, then raises his hand in an “OK” gesture, signaling approval.\n\nThe Pacer arrives at a large white mansion with tall columns, balconies, and a sweeping driveway. A formally dressed man in a black tuxedo and bow tie stands outside near the front steps, waiting. The yellow Pacer pulls up along the curb in front of the house and stops. The tuxedoed man remains poised in front of the grand entrance.\n\nFinally, the sandwich maker stands outdoors in front of the yellow AMC Pacer, holding the finished giant sandwich horizontally across his chest on a long tray. The sandwich is almost as wide as the car behind him. The cook faces forward in his white uniform and cap, while another person is partly visible behind him near the car. Large white on-screen text appears over the lower part of the image: “AMC Pacer,” with the AMC red-white-blue logo between the words. Beneath it, smaller text reads, “The first wide small car.” In the final image, the lower text changes to “Backed by the AMC Buyer Protection Plan,” while the cook continues holding the enormous sandwich in front of the parked yellow Pacer.",
